text:
Welcome to How To Cook That
I am Ann Reardon and we've got an exciting
episode for you this week.

A couple of weeks ago I asked you to nominate
all your favourite youtube channels.

I've tallied up the results and will make
the top ten for you today.

If a channel you requested is here make sure
you head on over to their channel and let

them know that How To Cook That made them
a cupcake.

First things first I made a batch of my perfect
sponge cake recipe into the cupcakes and topped

each one with a mixture of vanilla buttercream
and white chocolate ganache.

All of those recipes and their videos are
on this weeks blog post howtocookthat.net,

I'll put a link in the description just below
this video.
Starting at number 10.

We have RR cherry pie she has a mixture of
videos all about different cute and miniature
things.

To make her logo roll out some white and yellow
fondant cut out a small circle from the yellow

and take the circle bit out leaving the larger
bit in place.

Then take your white fondant over the top
and flip it over.

Then use a circle cutter that is one size
bigger than what we just used and cut it out.

So that gives us a yellow border all the way
around our white circle.

I am using soft sugar pearls and I bought
at the supermarket and I'm just pressing them
around the edge.

Then mix together some icing sugar red colour
and a tiny bit of water and use that to pipe
on the RR for RR cherry pie.

At number 9 is Surprise Kids - you asked for
it - Surprise Kids is my boys channel.

They don't really have a logo yet but their
thumbnail is a picture of one of them holding
a fin cookie that they made so we'll use that.

Cut out rectangles of white fondant and round
out the corners then roll an oval ball of

pale skin coloured fondant and squash it into
place.

Roll out some blue fondant and place it over
the bottom half and then trim it to the size
of the white.

Then using some store bought piping gel add
two eyes and a mouth.

Number 8 is Superwoman
"What up everybody it's your girl superwoman"

Lilly has a comedy channel, but a disclaimer
here some of her videos have adult themes

and are not suitable for a younger audience
if you are older then she has a super funny
channel you can check it out.

She recently came to Australia for youtube
fanfest and she did a great job on stage.

To make a superwoman logo print it out and
then cut it out, do not throw out any of those

little pieces because we are going to need
them.

Roll out some white fondant and rub it with
a tiny bit of oil.

And then place your paper with the logo sized
hole over the top.

Then add the superwoman logo bit and then
and put those tiny yellow pieces back into
place.

Peel off the red that was just there to guide
us where to put the yellow ones.

Then take some pink edible luster dust and
a dry paint brush and dust it on over the
top.

Then brush all the excess all over to one
side, you can reuse that, and carefully remove
the paper.

Put your circle cutter over the top and cut
it out.

Coming in at number 7 We have an Australian
you tuber My Cupcake Addiction she has just

had her second baby so make sure you head
over to her channel and say congratulations

and let her know How To Cook That made her
cupcake.

To make her logo cut out a circle of white
and then a smaller circle of pink.

Use your first larger cutter size to trim
off the top of the pink circle.

And then cut out a smaller white circle and
add it to your base then add the pink bit
on top of that.

Using some melted chocolate outline the shapes
and then add those curved stripes going towards
the centre at the bottom.

Take a tiny bit of red and roll it onto a
ball and add it on top like a cherry.

Number 6 most requested channel graveyard
girl "hey everybody it's bunny and welcome"

I like this channel too, Bunny does a great
job, it is sort of a beauty channel but totally
unique.

She has swamp family tea cups so that is what
we are going to make here.

Roll a snake of fondant and cut it off at
the top and the bottom.

Then run the knife around the top edge to
make an indent like a lid.
Then roll a tiny snake for a straw.

Take toothpick and make a hole in the top,
but don't add your straw right away leave
it for about and hour so it will dry out.

Once it's dried out then you can add a tiny
brush of water and put the straw in the top
of your swamp teacup.

Lets break from our top ten count here to
add in a little channel - you suggested loads

of small channels and they each had only one
suggestion so it took a while to choose which
one to do.

This one is called This Charming Stuff and
she makes cute charms out of polymer clay.

You can follow her tutorials and just swap
fondant instead of polymer clay and use it
on cakes.

Her logo is a cupcake to make it just roll
out some brown fondant into a ball then roll
it to make it narrower at one end.

Squash it down flatter until you get a cupcake
case shape.

Using a knife make indents all the way around
the case.

Take your green fondant and roll a long snake,
starting at the centre swirl it around and

around until you get to the top then twist
it off to give a nice piped look.

5 bethany mota
Bethany is just 18 years old and has a huge

beauty youtube channel on youtube and even
her own clothing line at aeropostale.

Until this week she has had this cute background
with a little photo and a cut camera but she's
just changed it.

So too late now because I've already made
her a cupcake.

Never mind, Lets make the cute camera, just
roll out some black fondant use a straw to
cut the circle and place it over the brown.

Use a black gel colour to outline it and then
cut out the camera shape.

For the photo I lust cut a rectangle of white
and put a faun rectangle on top.

Then rolled out a teardrop of pink and split
it at the top to make a heart and place that
onto the photo.

At number 4 we have the Shaytards
"We are a family of 6 and we have been making
daily videos for the last 4 years."

To make the profile of shays face print it
out and use a knife to indent key points onto

the fondant and then use black gel colour
to paint it on.

Shay carl started vlogging to document his
last year of being twenty, now 5 years on

he has millions of subscribers his wife and
kids all have their own channels, he was a

cofounder of maker studios a youtube network
that recently sold to Disney.

Number 3 is Zoella another beauty channel
"hello everybody today I am doing another

hairstyle for you" and she has clothing halls,
hair tutorials and makeup tutorials all of
those things.

Take some pink, white and green fondant and
roughly twist it together and then roll it
out.

Use your circle cutter to take a nice coloured
piece out.

And then take a printout of her logo put it
over the top and make an indent using a knife
so you know where to pipe.

Then take some melted chocolate pipe the word
Zoella onto the fondant.

At number 2 most requested by you was Nerdy
Nummies a channel by Rosanna Pansino welcome

to another nerdy nummies" where she makes
nerdy baked goods each week.

To make her logo cut out a circle of cookie
coloured fondant and then use melted chocolate
to pipe on some chocolate chips.

Take some black fondant and roll it super
thin place it across the cookie, trim it to

length and then take some more fondant and
make the glasses shape.

Ro was lucky enough to be one of the channels
recently promoted in a youtube ad campaign
all over New York and the subways and everywhere.

Take two balls of the black and roll them
into the circles for the eyeballs and squash

them into place and then take an even smaller
snake of black and put it in place for the
mouth.

Then roll two balls of pink and squash them
in place for those rosy cheeks.

OK lets pause the count again... you were
watching my channel so of course heaps and

heaps of you said you wanted How To Cook That
in it, so I am not going to count it in the
top ten but will show you how to make it.

Roll out some fondant then place the texture
mat over the top and push down using the roller.

Then just peel it off and you're left with
the pattern indented into the fondant.

Now for detailed logos you can get them printed
onto icing sheets like this.

You can buy a printer that's special with
edible ink and you can buy the special icing

paper or you can send your picture to a place
online that will print it for you which is
a much cheaper option.

Cut it out and rub gently on the back of it
to loosen the backing paper off it.
Dampen the fondant and add the logo on top.
Then use a circle cutter to cut around it.

And now drumroll the number 1 most requested
was of course Pewdiepie "They actually like

me, yeah brofist"
To make the bro fist print the logo and cut
around it in black fondant.

Roll a snake of blue and use that to make
the thumb shape and then the kind of m shape
as well.

Interestingly he is not the most subscribed
youtube channel though, youtube itself has

5 channels and they all collate top videos
in different categories.
But he's the number 1 youtuber.

I have to add a disclaimer here too because
his videos contain language and some gaming
content that is not suitable for children.

Add it to the black then use your knife to
squash it into place.

Place the black onto the white and cut it
out.

Roll a circle of blue and place the bro-fist
on top.

Add your cupcake toppers onto your cupcakes
and then you can serve them on a cupcake stand.

When you check out the channels make sure
you let them know that How To Cook That made

them a cupcake and if you haven't already
hit that subscribe button, do so, there is

a new cake, chocolate or dessert video every
week.

Add all your requests below check out the
channel here, last weeks jelly bean recipe
video is here and my website is here.
Have an awesome week and I'll see you on Friday.
